feat: phase 3 — BYOK-first, zero-cost operator model

The product pivot the user asked for: zero ongoing cost for the
operator, users pay Anthropic directly through their own API key.
ContentLoop is now a "we sell the prompt engineering, you bring
the LLM" product.

Changes

- /api/generate now requires either a server key OR a per-user BYOK
  key, otherwise returns 401 { byokRequired: true }. The default
  zero-cost deploy has no server key, so every user must add their
  own once.
- New /api/status endpoint: client reads it on workspace load to
  decide whether to force onboarding.
- New OnboardingModal: 3-step flow that pops on first visit if no
  key is set. Sends users to console.anthropic.com, accepts the
  pasted key, saves to localStorage. Anti-cliché copy explains the
  "$0.005–$0.02 per generation, you pay Anthropic" model upfront.
- Cost transparency: every successful generation aggregates token
  usage across formats and renders the actual USD spent (Sonnet 4.5
  pricing constants in lib/pricing.ts).
- Workspace "Generate" button gracefully swaps to a fuchsia "Add
  your API key to generate" CTA when no key is available.
- Landing repositioned:
  • Hero CTA reads "Open the app — bring your own key" when server
    has no key.
  • New "Bring your own key" section with 3-step explainer + real
    cost math ($0.09 per full 5-format run; $0.90/month for a
    heavy user).
  • Pricing flipped: Free = unlimited via BYOK. Pro = sync, brand
    kits, custom formats, bulk mode — premium tooling, not AI
    access. Pro price reset to $9/mo to match positioning.
  • FAQ expanded with BYOK questions ("why my own key?",
    "how much will my bill be?", "where is my key stored?").
- TipJar component: optional revenue stream that needs zero infra.
  Set NEXT_PUBLIC_TIP_JAR_URL to any link (ko-fi, BMC, GH Sponsors).
- README documents both deploy modes (pure BYOK vs hybrid free
  tier) and updated v0.3 roadmap entry.

Build clean, types pass, all 11 routes generate.
